# MongoDB - Users API (v2)
# Base: /api/v2/users
#
# IDs in MongoDB are ObjectIds - replace the placeholder below with a real one
# after running the POST request.
#
# @id = paste-a-real-objectid-here

### Read all users (MongoDB)
GET http://localhost:3002/api/v2/users

### Create a new user (MongoDB)
POST http://localhost:3002/api/v2/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Test Register2",
  "role": "user",
  "email": "test-register2@example.com",
  "password": "password1234"
}

### Login user (MongoDB)
POST http://localhost:3002/api/v2/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test-register2@example.com",
  "password": "password1234"
}


### Update a user (MongoDB) - replace the ObjectId with a real id from POST response
